column1: 1 Imports included in this table include dairy products assumed to be used as ingredients in domestically produced dairy products. It would be improper to add milk production (with a high water content) with imports of ingredients as displayed in this table (which includes only estimated milk solids).
2 Fluid milk volumes include only milk content, not other ingredients such as added sugar and flavorings.
3 Net totals are provided for certain products in order to avoid duplicate accounting due to the use of dairy products as ingredients in other dairy products.
4 "Yogurt, nonfrozen" includes yogurt components used in production of yogurt beverages.

5 For evaporated and condensed milk, gross rather than net volumes are reported in this table. However, net volumes are reported in the tables for milk fat and skim solids. The primary data source used for net accounting provides utilization data for these products on a milk-solids basis.

6For whey products and dry milk products, quantities estimated as “Less use in other dairy products” were based on preliminary estimates from the 2023 Dairy Products Utilization and Production Trends report published by the American Dairy Products Institute.
Source: USDA, Economic Research Service (ERS) calculations using data from numerous primary sources. See the USDA, ERS Dairy Data Documentation webpage for more details.
